description.narrative: As a result of UNICEF’s continued support to strengthening the justice for children system reform, the National Programme on prevention of offences among children and youth for 2020-2024 was approved by the Government of Tajikistan. The programme is based on Riyad Guidance and employs a child life-cycle approach. Another important milestone was reached in the area of prevention of violence against children (VAC) and sexual and gender-based violence (SGBV) against girls by establishment of cooperation between Ombudsperson for child rights (O4CR) and the Ministry of Education (MoES). | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:20/01/2022
